The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) in neural image captioning systems, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also compares different architectures for using RNNs in image captioning, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of these architectures, which could be considered information retrieval (cs.IR).
